CatDescriptText: Miss Edith Hollis, 327 Melwood Rd., Homestead, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that we are spending too much money for foreign aid? Do you think that what we have spent has halted the spread of communism?" answer reads: "I don't think so.  I think that we need good international relations and foreign aid is the way to improve our relations with other countries.  I think that it has halted the spread of communism."
